title: S. Jersey Girls: S.J. girls: Moorestown wins Central Jersey tennis crown
text:
South Non-Public A Final. Caitlyn Sorelle, Caitlin Deffler and Ashley Sorelle won their singles matches in straight sets to lead host No. 1 Bishop Eustace to a 4-1 win over No. 2 Red Bank Catholic. Girls' Soccer 
Jillian Calhoun,Nina Nelson and Quinn Nicolai scored three straight goals in the second half to lift host Moorestown over Cinnaminson, 3-2, in a Burlington County League match. Nicolai had the winner with six minutes left. Moorestown is ranked ninth in South Jersey by The Inquirer; Cinnaminson is 10th. 
Elsewhere in the Burlington County League: 
Michelle Knope, MeKayla Montgomery, Kelly Moss and Caroline Rockhill scored and Rancocas Valley won at Northern Burlington, 4-3. Theresa Adu-Attobrah made 14 saves. 
Olympic. Sude Yalcin scored the winner, and No. 4 Lenape shut out host No. 7 Bishop Eustace, 1-0. Shannon Mulroy stopped four shots. 
Silvana Gordon scored twice, as No. 2 Shawnee defeated host Cherry Hill West, 4-0. Christina Corbi and Julzz Bertolino also scored. 
Emily Gray had a goal and two assists in No. 3 Washington Township's 4-0 victory over visiting Paul VI. Kylie D'Ambra, Madison Dorney and Natasha Munro also scored. 
Cape-Atlantic. Morgan Giordano netted the winner to give Millville a 1-0 victory at Mainland in double overtime. Giordano scored the goal on a rebound of her own shot that the hit the post just more than a minute into the second overtime. 
Colonial. Sam Budd scored four times and added an assist to lead host West Deptford to a 6-1 win over Collingswood. Caroline Perry had three assists. Field Hockey 
Tatiana Woods scored in the second half, and Schalick defeated host Deptford, 1-0, in a Tri-County match. Sarah Hatten made five saves. 
In other Tri-County Diamond games: 
Destini Parker scored twice to help host Delsea to a 3-1 win over Woodstown. Nadia Berardelli also scored. 
S'Deionna Washington had a hat trick and three assists to power host Salem to a 6-1 win over Penns Grove. Ayanna Chapman scored twice. 
Olympic. Drew Pecora scored twice to help Bishop Eustace to a 4-1 victory at Lenape. Ashley Conklin and Erin Quinn also scored. Volleyball 
Caitlin Lange had six kills, two aces, one block, and had nine service points to help host Seneca to a 2-0 victory against Camden. Seneca clinched a share of the Olympic Conference Freedom Division title for the first time.
